Sure, here are some examples:

1. *Riknula* je jabuka na drvetu. (*Riknula* - past tense of "riknuti" - "The apple rotted on the tree.")
2. Moja majka ne voli kad *riknem* na ispitu. (*Riknem* - present tense of "riknuti" - "My mother doesn't like it when I fail an exam.")
3. Dok sam pekla hleb, čula sam kako nešto *riče* u dvorištu. (*Riče* - present tense of "ričati" - "While I was baking bread, I heard something roaring in the yard.")
4. Krave su počele da *riču* kad su vidjele farmera. (*Riču* - present tense of "ričati" - "The cows started mooing when they saw the farmer.")
5. Ova stara kuća je *rikava* i treba joj temeljito renoviranje. (*Rikava* - adjective form of "riknuti" - "This old house is dilapidated and needs thorough renovation.")
6. Čuli smo *riku* jelena u šumi. (*Rika* - noun form of "ričati" - "We heard the roar of a deer in the woods.")
7. U mom selu ima mnogo ljudi koji se bave *rikom* ribe. (*Rika* - noun form of "ričati" - "In my village, there are many people who are involved in the fish trade.")
8. Nekoliko dana nakon što smo posadili cvijeće, primijetili smo da su neke biljke već *rikle*. (*Rikle* - past participle form of "riknuti" - "A few days after we planted the flowers, we noticed that some plants had already died.")

I hope this helps!